	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Like their incorrectly wired consoles, the Yobo converters connect chr /a13 and ciram /ce together.  Notice how on the front pict there are 2 sets of bridged pins.  One is for audio bypass (correct) and the other is ciram enable (wrong).
<br />
<br />Of course if no games are working it is a different problem.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


